A '''video card''' is a piece of [[hardware]] installed into a [[computer system]] to allow it to send [[video]] [[signals]] to an external output [[device]] such as a [[monitor]], a [[television set]] or a [[video display]].  

Note that while many [[computer system]]s come with a video [[adapter]] and the circuitry for communicating with an external output device is built into the [[motherboard]] of the computer system, there are video cards sold separately for enhanced video capability in certain demanding applications such as [[computer-assisted design]] and [[video game]]s.